<HEADLINE> U.N. Chief Names ICTY Prosecutor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 6 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan has named Carla Del Ponte as prosecutor of the
International Tribunal for Former Yugoslavia (ICTY) and the
International Criminal Tribunal for Rwanda, his spokesman said
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Carla del Ponte, 52, is currently the attorney general of
Switzerland. She will succeed Canadian Louise Arbour who has
recently announced her resignation as she takes up the position as
a judge of the Supreme Court of Canada in September.
</P>
<P>
No date has been set yet for the Security Council to take action
on the nomination by Annan Thursday. A formal resolution by the
council will be needed for the appointment to take effect which is
scheduled for September 15. 
</P>
</TEXT>
