<HEADLINE> Zhang Upsets World No. 3 Li Ju in Quarters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
EINDHOVEN, Netherlands, August 6 (Xinhua) -- China's inexhaustible
source of young promising and future champions in table tennis was
proved as two 17-year-olds romped into the women's singles semifinals
at the world table tennis championships here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Yining upset China's world No. 3 and second seed Li Ju
21-13, 21-10, 21-13, while Li Nan nipped teammate Sun Jin 21-23,
21-12, 21-18, 21-18.
</P>
<P>
In the other all Chinese quarter-final, Wang Nan downed Cheng
Hongxia 21-17, 21-15, 21-12.
</P>
<P>
South Korean Ryu Ji Hae also made the last four with a 18-21,
21-17, 21-16, 21-9 win over German Jing Tian-Zorner. 
</P>
</TEXT>
