<HEADLINE> Uganda to Eradicate Poverty by 2017: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- A revised poverty eradication
action plan will enable Uganda to eradicate mass poverty from its
society by the year 2017, Ugandan Deputy Secretary to Treasury
Chris Kassami said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The official made the remarks at the launch of a poverty status
report and national participatory assessment.
</P>
<P>
The poverty eradication action plan will be revised to reflect
the concerns and priority of the poor, Ugandan Vice President
Specioza Kazibwe said in a speech read for her at the function.
</P>
<P>
The vice president said that the plan will ensure improved food
security and sustainable livelihood of the poor and create an
enabling environment for larger scale commercial agriculture,
Radio Uganda reported.
</P>
<P>
The vice president also said that the government is to finalize
a policy framework for the modernization of agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The framework will spell out guiding principles and
institutional roles for implementing the plan, she was quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
A communication strategy is being developed for disseminating
principles and results of government policy for poverty
eradication, she added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
