<HEADLINE> Zambia Confident of Local Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Local manufacturing firms and
industries have been commended for displaying high quality
products at the just ended 73rd Zambia Agriculture and Commercial
Show.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Minister of Commerce, Trade and Industry, Jazzman
Chikwakwa, said here Friday that there was great improvement in
the quality of products exhibited at the show compared to last
year.
</P>
<P>
He said the government is now confident of the fact that
Zambian products can now compete effectively with imported ones.
</P>
<P>
Chikwakwa said when Zambia's trade agreement with Southern
African Custom Union (SACU), products from here have to be of high
quality to compete on the market.
</P>
<P>
He further pointed out that local manufacturers should never
complain about unfair competition from imported. The just ended
agriculture show has dominated by local firms as most foreign
firms did not make it.
</P>
<P>
According to the statistics obtained from the show society
officials the number of participants this year had increased by
112 from 620 recorded last year.
</P>
<P>
Among the 732 participants, 10 are foreign countries, 670 local
 exhibitors and 52 individual foreign companies.
</P>
<P>
Locally produced goods were mainly those from the agriculture
sector and major local exhibitors were those in the commercial and
services industry like those in the banking and telecommunications
industry.
</P>
<P>
Other locally manufactured goods were from the small and medium
scale manufacturers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
