<HEADLINE> OAU to Deliver Peace Plan to Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- A special delegation of the
Organization of African Unity (OAU) arrived here from Algeria
Friday to deliver a detailed peace plan on resolving the
Ethio-Eritrea crisis to the Ethiopian government.
</P>
<P>
Algerian envoy Ahmed Ouyhia, head of the delegation, is
expected to deliver the document to Ethiopian Prime Minister Meles
Zenawi, according to a spokesman for the Ethiopian Ministry of
Foreign Affairs.
</P>
<P>
Prior to its arrival, the OAU delegation had visited Eritrea,
the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Informed sources said that the detailed OAU peace plan calls
for the withdrawal of the Eritrean forces from all occupied
Ethiopian territories.
</P>
<P>
The 14-month conflict broke out between Ethiopia and Eritrea
over border disputes in May last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
