<HEADLINE> Angola Makes New Relief Program for War Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Angolan government made this decision in a session of the
Permanent Committee of the Council of Ministers held in Luanda
Friday, presided by the President of Angola Jose Eduardo dos
Santos.
</P>
<P>
A communique issued Friday by the committee said the government
hopes the new relief program will help relieve the suffering of
the displaced people.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that up to half of the allocation will be used
to buy food for the victims living in besieged cities, while other
three million dollars will be appropriated for the self-sufficient
production by the displaced people.
</P>
<P>
On July 15, the government decided to adopt an "emergency
strategy" of humanitarian aids, providing with potato seeds and
other agricultural materials for residents of the besieged cities
and encouraging them to do farm work.
</P>
<P>
The committee, consisting of nine important ministries of the
cabinet, is responsible in wartime for dealing with issues on
military, politics, social problems and economic crisis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
