<HEADLINE> Annan to Attend 50th Anniversary Commemoration of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 6 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan is scheduled to be in Geneva on August 11-12 to take
part in the commemoration of the 50th anniversary of the Geneva
Conventions, a U.N. news release said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Annan will be among those signing a Solemn Appeal at the
Alabama Room of the Geneva Town Hall and later speaking at a
ceremony marking the event on the morning of August 13 at the
"Batiment des forces metrices."
</P>
<P>
The ceremony is organized by the International Committee of the
Red Cross jointly with the Swiss Government, the Republic and
Canton of Geneva in the City of Geneva, said the news release.
</P>
<P>
The Secretary-General has frequently highlighted the
importance of the four Geneva Conventions, which were signed in
1949, terming them the most comprehensive efforts to define what
constitutes acceptable behavior in war time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
