<HEADLINE> 2 Chinese Pairs Make Men's Doubles Semis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
EINDHOVEN, Netherlands, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Olympic champions Liu
Guoliang and Kong Linghui fought a five-set thriller to beat Austrian
duo Werner Schlager and Karl Jinkdrak in the men's doubles
quarter-finals of the world table tennis championships here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
After taking first two sets 21-19, 21-15, the top-seeded Chinese
combination appeared slack and lost the following two sets 21-19,
21-15.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese, who lagged behind most of the deciding set, held their
nerves to win 25-23.
</P>
<P>
Wang Liqin and Yan Sen won a second semifinal berth for China as
they subdued Chiang Peng-Lung and Chang Yuan-Su from Chinese Taipei,
24-22, 16-21, 21-15, 21-18.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ma Lin and Zhang Yingying won the mixed doubles title with
a 21-15, 21-19, 9-21, 21-15 victory over teammates Feng Zhe and Sun Jin.
</P>
<P>
In the women's doubles quarter-finals, top seeds Wang Nan and Li Ju
of China ousted Hungary's Csilla Batorfi and Krisztina Toth 21-9,
21-18, 21-16.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Zhang Yining/Zhang Yingying and Yang Ying/Sun Jin also
reached the last four.
</P>
<P>
The remaining semifinal berth went to Park Hae Jung/Kim Moo Kyo of
South Korea, who thumped Cheng Jing/Xu Jing of Chinese Taipei, 19-21,
12-21, 21-18, 23-21, 21-18. 
</P>
</TEXT>
