<HEADLINE> Annan Names Representative for U.N. Year of Dialogue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 6 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan Friday named Giandomenico Picco as his personal
representative for the United Nations Year of Dialogue among
Civilizations in 2001.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. General Assembly set 2001 as the year of the theme on
November 4, 1998 and invited governments and the U.N. system to
plan programs to promote this concept.
</P>
<P>
The announcement underlines the importance which the
secretary-general attaches to the event, his spokesman Fred
Eckhard told reporters.
</P>
<P>
On behalf of the secretary-general, Picco will launch
initiatives aimed at furthering the dialogue among civilizations.
</P>
<P>
Picco, a citizen of Italy, once served as U.N. assistant
secretary-general for political affairs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
