<HEADLINE> Four People Killed in U.S. Plane Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 6 (Xinhua) -- All four people aboard a
single-engine plane were killed when it clipped a power line and
plunged into a field Thursday night in Lake County in Illinois
State of the United States, said reports reaching here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The man at the controls was an experienced pilot, the reports
quoted Lake County Coroner Barbara Richardson as saying.
</P>
<P>
Authorities said he had taken two men and a woman on a
three-hour excursion flight and was returning to Campbell Airport
when the plane crashed.
</P>
<P>
The crash downed power lines, delaying emergency crews trying
to reach the scene, according to the reports. 
</P>
