<HEADLINE> U.S. Firefighters Step Up Fighting Wildfires </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Hundreds of U.S. firefighters
Friday stepped up fighting wildfires that blackened over 1,400
kilometers of Nevada range, threatening ranches and historic
buildings.
</P>
<P>
In the past few days, thousands of lightning strikes from
storms sparked some 80 fires across northern Nevada State in the
west United States.
</P>
<P>
The fires were estimated to have burned 240,000 hectares by
early Friday, an area nearly the size of Rhode Island in the east
United States. No injuries were reported and only one structure --
a storage shed -- was destroyed.
</P>
<P>
About 1,700 more firefighters were shipped in from around the
country Thursday, bringing the total by Friday morning to 2,500
with more on the way. The battle was expected to extend into the
weekend. 
</P>
</TEXT>
