<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000GMT, Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA -- Ignoring pressures from several European countries
and human rights groups, Vural Savas, the chief prosecutor of
Turkey's High Court of Appeals, asked the court to uphold the
death penalty for PKK leader Abdullah Ocalan.
</P>
<P>
Ocalan, leader of the outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK),
was sentenced to death on June 29 on charges of treason and
separatism.
</P>
<P>
Ocalan-led PKK has been waging a separatist campaign in
southeastern Turkey since 1984. Conflicts between the Turkish
security forces and the PKK rebels have claimed over 37,000
lives. (BC-Turkey-PKK)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- A personal envoy of Israeli Prime Minister Ehud
Barak has met with Palestinian National Authority (PNA) Chairman
Yasser Arafat in an effort to establish a private channel of
contact between the two leaders, local daily Haaretz reported on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The envoy is reserve Brigadier General Yitzhak Segev, a former
military governor of the Gaza Strip and an attache of Israeli army
in Iran during the period of the Shah's rule.
(BC-Israel-Palestine-Envoy)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NICOSIA -- Cyprus is to receive six TOR-M1 short-range missile
systems from Greece as part of the exchange for the long-range
Russian S-300 missiles now deployed in Greece's Crete island,
local media reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus' National Guard will receive the first batch of the 21
missile systems once Greece gets them from Moscow.
</P>
<P>
However, Cypriot army's top officials are reportedly concerned
about the island's air defense because the short-range missiles
cannot reach Turkish airspace for preemptive strikes.
(BC-Cyprus-Missiles)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
GAZA -- Palestinian National Authority (PNA) asked for United
States intervention for a fair and precise implementation of the
Wye Accord, PNA chief negotiator Saed Erekat has said.
</P>
<P>
Several contacts were made with U.S. Special Envoy to the
Middle East Denis Ross and other officials and "we asked their
help so as to ensure honest and timely implementation of the Wye
Agreement because U.S. is a key sponsor of the peace process,"
Erekat was quoted by the Arabic daily Al-Ayam published Friday.
(BC-Palestine-Accord)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran has said it is inviting the Taliban and its
opposition forces in Afghanistan to implement agreements reached
at the "six plus two" meeting in Tashkent, Uzbekistan in July.
</P>
<P>
The ongoing conflicts in Afghanistan have no military solution,
Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal Kharrazi said to the official
Islamic Republic News Agency here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Afghanistan's six neighbors - China, Iran, Pakistan,
Tajikistan, Uzbekistan and Turkmenistan - and the United States
and Russia, well-known as the "six plus two" informal group, have
agreed to improve coordination and efforts for a common approach
toward the settlement of the Afghan crisis. (BC-Iran-Afghanistan)
</P>
</TEXT>
