<HEADLINE> U.N. Begins Deploying Police in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
announced Friday that it will begin deploying international police
monitors in Kosovo over the weekend, with the first officers to be
placed in Pristina, where the crime rate is extremely high.
</P>
<P>
There are currently 474 out of an expected 3100 international
police in Kosovo with the mandate of enforcing law and order.
</P>
<P>
They are also charged with establishing and training a Kosovo
Police Service, a U.N. spokesman quoted the U.N. Police
Commissioner in Kosovo Sven Fredericksen as saying. 
