<HEADLINE> Five Killed, Eight Injured in Pakistan Road Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Five people were killed and
eight seriously injured on Saturday when a speeding truck ran over
a wagon in Pakistan's Punjab province.
</P>
<P>
According to police sources, the truck went out of control
after one of its tyres burst and it ran over the wagon parked
along the roadside before ramming into a tree.
</P>
<P>
The wagon loaded with passengers was badly damaged. Four
passengers died instantly and nine others including the truck
driver were seriously injured.
</P>
<P>
One of the injured died in hospital. 
</P>
