<HEADLINE> Pan Am Success Makes up for Malar's Olympic Failure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WINNIPEG, Canada, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Joanne Malar wears a
gold ring on the second toe of her left foot to remind her how far
she has come since the depressing days after the 1996 Olympics
when she failed to get to the medal podium.
</P>
<P>
The gold ring was there as the 23-year-old Canadian swimmer
bent to get her third gold medal of the 13th Pan American Games
draped around her neck last night.
</P>
<P>
Malar broke the Pan Am and Canadian records in winning the 200m
individual medley. Her time was two minutes 14.18 seconds.
</P>
<P>
"The ring represents a healing time for me, " Malar said. "I
was down after the 1996 Olympics and went to Mexico with my sister
and my sister's friend. It was two weeks where I could just be
Joanne and not to be overwhelmed by pressures and expectations.
</P>
<P>
"I look at it, and it reminds me of the things I went through."
she said.
</P>
<P>
Those things included failing to make the final in her
specialty race, the 400m individual medley. It set a tone that
later saw Malar drop off a relay squad and finish fourth in the
200m.
</P>
<P>
The Atlanta Games can never be retrieved, but Malar looks ahead.
She has changed her coach and club and altered her training. At
the national training center in Calgary, in the company of Olympic
medalists such as Curtis Myden, Shamek Pietucha, Morgan Knabe and
Penny Heyns of South Africa, she has trained with weights and
improved her balance and strength by working out standing on a
ball.
</P>
<P>
"I feel like I should be in the circus, " Malar said.
</P>
<P>
"It's good to know I'm not doing it alone, " she said of the
training group. "There's times when one of us is hurting and
someone can pull you aside and help you through it."
</P>
<P>
Canada now has 25 medals in 26 races at Winnipeg, including 11
gold, four silver and 10 bronze. Canada's record haul from the Pan
Am pool is 28, achieved in 1967 in Winnipeg and matched in 1979 in
San Juan.
</P>
<P>
Malar had only four swims at the Pan Am Games, netting her
other golds in the 400 individual medley and 4X200m relay and
getting a bronze in the 400m freestyle.
</P>
<P>
Her stunning collection of Pan Am hardware, dating back to 1991
in Havana, also includes seven silver and three bronze medals.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
