people from all over Zimbabwe to capital Harare in February sought
to outline political, economic and social factors which the
government had failed to resolve.
</P>
<P>
Among the issues that were discussed during the convention were
the drawing up of a new constitution, the need to reduce inflation
and to have complementary monetary and fiscal policies,
resettlement of people, gender equality, press freedom, the right
to health and the need for a housing policy.
</P>
<P>
