<HEADLINE> Guangzhou to Build Software Development Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 7 (Xinhua) -- This capital of South China's
Guangdong Province plans to inject four billion yuan (about 482
million U.S. dollars) into the development of computer software
over the next five years.
</P>
<P>
A software development and production base will be constructed
at the Guangzhou Tianhe Hi-Tech Garden, home to 93 software
companies, which account for about half of the software
enterprises in the province and whose annual sales revenue from
software is reported to be over one billion yuan, or one tenth of
the national figure.
</P>
