<HEADLINE> Industrial Sector Tianjin's Driving Force </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Industrial production has become
the leading driving force in the economy of north China's Tianjin
municipality, contributing seven percent to its economic growth
during the first six months of this year.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin 's industrial output reached 30.2 billion yuan-worth
during the first half of the year, a rise of 13 percent over the
same 1998 period.
</P>
<P>
The sector also reported an improvement in efficiency during
the period, with industrial profits rising year-on-year by 18
percent, to eight billion yuan, and losses incurred by deficit-
ridden enterprises declining by eight percent on a yearly basis.
</P>
<P>
This promising situation can be mainly attributed to the State'
s stimulatory policies aimed at increasing domestic demand.
Enterprises manufacturing products such as electric wire, metal
items, tires, steel, concrete and hydro-power generators have at
least doubled their output during the period.
</P>
<P>
The production of high-tech products also received a great
boost, with the output of integrated circuits, switchboards,
mobile phones and personal computers registering year-on-year
increases ranging from six to 66 percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the emergence of some new projects has served as a
new growth point for local industrial production. Statistics show
that 12 such projects brought in about 3.3 billion yuan in output
value during the first six months.
</P>
<P>
The ten major enterprise groups in Tianjin have also become a
major underpinning for the rapid industrial growth, with
successful technological renovations and deepened reform. The
average output growth for these ten enterprises stood at 13
percent during the January-June period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
