<HEADLINE> Troop Movements, Weapon Supplies to Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The peace efforts by the
Organization of African Unity (OAU) and the Arab league seem to be
making some progress in the Ethiopia-Eritrea war which has spilled
over to Somalia.
</P>
<P>
Both foreign troop movements and the infusion of mass weapon
supplies into Somalia are being minimized, if not stopped totally.
</P>
<P>
One concrete example is the failure of warlord Muse Sudi
Yalahow to smuggle weapons and ammunition into Somalia from
Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the week, Yalahow went to Hiran region for a
possible reception of weapons and ammunition from Ethiopia. Muse
Sudi's convoy together with other battle wagons from the Hawadleh
clan have gone all the way to Fer-fer village on the
Somali-Ethiopian border to meet Ethiopian military officers for
the hand-over of the weapons and ammunition.
</P>
<P>
After undisclosed two-day discussions between representatives
of Yalahow, Hawadleh clan military officers and Ethiopian
officials, the convoy returned to Mogadishu Friday empty handed.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for Yalahow has denied the arrival of any weapons
or ammunition as reported by a local daily newspaper. The
spokesman said the convoy did not come from Ethiopia in the first
place, but that his battle wagons had merely escorted commercial
lorries to the central regions and escorted others back to
Mogadishu and therefore had nothing to do with weapon reception
from Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
On the other front, despite the presence of Ethiopian troops in
Bay and Bakol regions, their movements seem to have stopped at
least temporarily.
</P>
<P>
According to unconfirmed reports, the Ethiopians have stopped
supplying weapons and ammunition to the Rahanwein Resistance Army
(RRA) and their affiliated new group of Digil Salvation Army
fighting against faction leader Hussein Mohamed Aidid in Lower
Shabelle region, southern Somalia.
</P>
<P>
Political analysts said the Ethiopians are probably honoring
the peace tentative of the OAU and that if fails they will
continue their operations inside Somalia and even more seriously.
</P>
<P>
Aidid has told his supporters that mediation efforts between
his faction and Ethiopia are underway. He said he is going to lead
a delegation to Tripoli of Libya for the mediation efforts.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
