<HEADLINE> Vietnam Enhances Export of Aquatic Produce </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's fisheries sector has been
enhancing the export of aquatic produce, Vietnam News Agency
reported on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam has earned export revenues of more than 502 million
U.S. dollars in the first seven months of this year, a 10 percent
increase over the same period last year, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's cultivation and breeding of aquatic produce has
developed steadily throughout the country and the sector produced
329,000 tons of seafood from aquaculture alone.
</P>
<P>
It has brought the country's total output so far this year to
more than 1 million tons.
</P>
<P>
And more seafood processing enterprises nationwide have
invested in shrimp farming projects.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam hopes to increase its shrimp exports to Japan this year
thanks to the reduction in Japanese levies. 
