<HEADLINE> India to Double SAARC Investment Ceiling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The Indian government has
decided to double the ceiling for overseas Indian investments in
SAARC (South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation) to 30
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to the Reserve Bank of India (RBI), the government
has also increased rupee investments in Nepal and Bhutan to 1.2
billion rupees (27.9 million U.S. dollars) from 600 million rupees
(13.95 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
