<HEADLINE> Printing House Fined for Copyright Infringement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- A printing house in this Chinese
capital has been fined 50,000 yuan and its two leading officials
fined 10,000 yuan each and sentenced to two years in prison for
infringement of the copyright of a children's encyclopedia.
</P>
<P>
This is the first case involving a legal person since the
implementation of the revised Criminal Law.
</P>
<P>
The defendant, the Beijing Gaoling Printing House, signed a
contract with publisher Dai Guanghao, and illegally printed 15,500
volumes of a children's encyclopedia the exclusive publisher of
which is the Zhejiang Educational Publishing House in east China's
Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
Dai Guanghao was fined 150,000 yuan and sentenced to seven
years in prison on the same charge on March 15 this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
