Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- The actions of merging and take-over by the world's big
companies are increasing, as three gigantic transactions were made
on Friday alone, with 24.7 billion U.S. dollars changing hand in
one single day. The German telecoms company, Deutsche Telekom
bought 100 percent of the capital of One-2-One, Britain's fourth
largest telephone operator with 13.4 billion U.S. dollars. The
two Swedish automakers, Volvo and Scania, merged with each, while
the U.S. General Motors set up a "strategic alliance" with South
Korea's Daewoo.
</P>
<P>
-- France has warned the United States against a possible
destabilization in the East Asia region with the envisaged U.S.-
sponsored DMT system in the region. French Foreign Minister
Hubert Vedrine has written to his U.S. counterpart Madeleine
Albright, expressing France's concern over a possible
deterioration of the situation in East Asia. 
