<HEADLINE> Second Ethnic Museum Opens in Inner Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, August 7 (Xinhua) -- A museum featuring the history
and traditions of the Mongolian people has been opened in a
township in the western Tsab area of the Inner Mongolia Autonomous
Region.
</P>
<P>
The second township-level museum in the region, the museum has
on display over 80 exhibits,including fossilized footprints of
dinosaurs, fossilized fishes, and ancient engravings, saddles,
boots, bows, arrows and embroidery works.
</P>
<P>
The area is famous for its deeply rooted Mongolian traditions.
</P>
<P>
The first township ethnic museum in the region is located in
the northeastern part of Inner Mongolia, featuring the traditions
and culture of the nomadic Mongol people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
