<HEADLINE> World-class Stars to Shine at Military World Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, Croatia, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Military discipline and
tough training have helped to create countless sports stars and a
lot of them are set to shine at the Military World Games to open
here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The sports they are competing range from swimming, judo to less
known lifesaving but nonetheless these stars had triumphed in
events like world championships, world cup or Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
When the accuracy of aiming is no longer the matter of life and
death, elite shooters from around the globe will vie for medals
here.
</P>
<P>
They include China's Atlanta Olympics women's sports pistol
champion Li Duihong, Slovenian rifle expert Rajmond Debevec,
Poland's Olympic titlist Renata Mauer and Russia's Marina
Logvinenko, who won the gold in air pistol at Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
World powerhouse Russia will make a big splash in the pools as
it sends the country's top diving aces Dmitry Sautin and Irina
Lashko plus Olympic swimming champion Denis Pankratov.
</P>
<P>
The Russians also have great strength in their fencing team,
which is spearheaded by Pavel Kolobkov, Stanislav Pozdnyakov and
Dmitri Shevchenko, each of them winning world championship for
several times.
</P>
<P>
China will field its mighty military pentathlon squad, which
has won both the men's and the women's team titles at the 1998
world championships. 
</P>
