<HEADLINE> Storm Disrupts Railway Traffic in Southeast France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 7 (Xinhua) -- A big storm greatly disrupted the
railway transports in the region of Chambery in southeast France
Saturday morning, said the French state railway company SNCF.
</P>
<P>
A train going from Grenoble to Veynes in the Alps region bumped
into a bush lying on the track, but no one was injured in the
accident, said the SNCF.
</P>
<P>
Violent wind pulled down many trees along the railway tracks,
including those of high speed trains, disrupting the timetable of
three high speed trains.
</P>
<P>
The departure of many trains was disrupted Saturday morning in
the region, mainly because of the damages done to the railway
tracks in the region of Dijon in the north during the storm.
</P>
