<HEADLINE> Cuba Pulls Away from Canada with Five Boxing Golds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WINNIPEG, Canada, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Cuba out-boxed their
opponents mercilessly to bag home five gold here on Friday, which
helped them to pull away from hosts Canada in the medals count at
the Pan Am Games.
</P>
<P>
M.Romero, M.Kindelan, Juan Hernandez, Yohason Martinzez and
Odlaniel Solis triumphed in 48kg, 60kg, 67kg, 75kg and 91kg
respectively, boosting Cuba's gold medal tally to 62 against third-
placed Canada's 52.
</P>
<P>
The United States, whose athletes won gold in swimming,
Taekwondo, boxing and archery, kept their tight control over the
top spot with an unbeatable 92 golds.
</P>
<P>
Hosts Canada continued their superb form at the Pan Am Pool,
grabbing a pair of golds here today to lift their swimming gold
tally to 11.
</P>
<P>
Canada's Joanne Malar broke the Games record twice en route to
her second gold medal at the Pan Am Pool, winning the women's 200m
medley race in 2:14.18 here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The home favourite raised the packed house to its feet as she
shattered her own record of 2:14.81, which was just set in the
morning's preliminaries, and added another gold to her 400m medley
title from August 2.
</P>
<P>
In the men's 200m butterfly final, P.Pietucha of Canada failed
to improve his own record of 1:58.50, which was also established
in the morning's prelims on his way to the gold medal. His time
stood at 1:59.10.
</P>
<P>
In the weightlifting competitions, Dominican Wanda Rijo hoisted
the country to its first gold medal after their high jumper Juana
Rosario Arrende had her title stripped of following a positive
drug test.
</P>
<P>
In the women's 75kg class, Rijo lifted 100kg in the snatch and
120kg in the clean and jerk for a combined result of 220kg,
beating American rival Cara Heads's 217.5kg into second spot.
</P>
<P>
In the synchronized swimming, the Canadian pair C.Carver-Dias
and Fanny Letourneau garnered a total of 97.289 points to capture
the gold.
</P>
<P>
In the men's basketball semi-finals, Brazil scored a 95-85
victory over Puerto Rico to advance to the final, where they will
take on the United States, a 84-76 winners over Argentina.
</P>
