<HEADLINE> Cholera Claims 162 Lives in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- A total of 162 people have died
of cholera in Uganda this year, an official with the Ministry of
Health has said.
</P>
<P>
Sam Okware, commissioner for communicable diseases, said Friday
that 3, 298 cases have been reported countrywide, the New Vision
newspaper reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Since the epidemic was first reported in December 1997, about
2,201 patients have died and 52,461 cases have been recorded, said
the report.
</P>
<P>
Okware, who is the head of the National Cholera Task Force,
noted that over 173 patients have been admitted at cholera centers
in several districts around the country over the last two weeks.
</P>
<P>
The most affected areas are in Mbarara in southwestern Uganda.
The disease is also reported in areas bordering Sudan and the
Democratic Republic of Congo. 
