<DOCNO> XIE19990807.0159 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-07 09:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuwaiti Crown Prince to Visit Egypt in September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The Kuwaiti crown prince is
expected to pay a visit to Egypt in early September, Egypt's
Al-Akhbar daily reported on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Sheikh Saad Al-Abdullah Al-Salem Al-Sabah
will hold talks with Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak and Prime
Minister Kamal El-Ganzouri on regional issues, including the
situation in the Gulf and the Middle East peace process, the
pro-government newspaper quoted Egyptian Ambassador to Kuwait
Mahmoud Wagdy as saying.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Saad, who is also the Kuwaiti prime minister, will
discuss with Egyptian leaders ways of seeking close cooperation in
economic and trade areas, Wagdy said.
</P>
<P>
The visit comes within the context of constant consultations
and coordination between the two countries, the Egyptian
ambassador said.
</P>
<P>
Egypt and Kuwait maintain close and good relations after Cairo
sided with Kuwait in the 1990 Gulf crisis and joined the
multinational forces in the 1991 Gulf War to liberate Kuwait from
the occupation of Iraqi troops.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have signed many agreements on cooperation in
the fields of economy, technology, tourism, science, information
and labor.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian-Kuwaiti trade volume stood at 118 million U.S.
dollars in 1998. Kuwait has invested in Egypt an estimated 840
million dollars by the end of 1997, making it the second largest
Arab investor in Egypt after Saudi Arabia.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Kuwait's Arab Fund for Development provided Egypt
with loans totaling over 1 billion dollars in the past five
years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
