<HEADLINE> Tourist Arrivals Increase in Maldives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The tourists visiting the
Maldives in the first half of this year increased by 11.7 percent
compared with the same period last year, reports reaching here
from Male said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
During the period there were 216,351 tourists in comparison
with 193,712 during the corresponding period last year, the
reports said.
</P>
<P>
The highest number of tourist arrivals was from Italy,
accounting for 22 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
The Maldives' Ministry of Tourism estimated that the total
number of tourists to arrive in the country by the end of this
year would be over 437,700, the reports added.
</P>
<P>
A total of 390,000 tourists visited the Maldives last year.
</P>
