<HEADLINE> ADB to Provide Loan For Colombo Port Expansion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
will provide a loan of 240 million U.S. dollars to expand the
Queen Elizabeth Quay of the Colombo Port in the capital of Sri
Lanka, Port Authority sources said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Sri Lankan government hoped the Colombo Port would become
the main hub-port in the Asian region.
</P>
<P>
The expansion project, which is due to take place in two
stages, will increase the Colombo Port's container handling
capacity by 40 percent, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The South Asian Gateway Terminals Ltd. (SAGT) leases the QEQ
which was handed over to the SAGT by the Sri Lankan government for
thirty years under an agreement signed here Friday night.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, the SAGT, whose primary partner is
P&AMP;O Australia LTD., will pay a lease of 2 million U.S. dollars per
annum to the Sri Lankan Ports Authority. 
</P>
</TEXT>
