<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rafter Falls to Kiefer at Canadian Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Nicolas Kiefer of Germany upset
the defending champion Patrick Rafter of Australia on Friday at
the quarter-finals of the Canadian Open tennis for the third time
in as many meetings.
</P>
<P>
Kiefer showed his strength in baseline play in a 6-3, 6-7 (5-7),
7-6 (7-4) beat the top seed whose serve-and-volley game failed to
work during the two hours and 43 minutes battle.
</P>
<P>
Rafter did keep himself stay in contention as he rallied from 1-
5 down in the second-set tiebreaker,and from 1-3 behind in the
third set to eventually force a final-set tiebreak against Kiefer.
</P>
<P>
With points at four apiece in the tiebreak, the Australian
first netted a forehand volley and then a forehand service return
before Kiefer finished off a rousing battle by acing Rafter on his
first match point.
</P>
<P>
Second-seeded American Andre Agassi also advanced to the semi-
finals with a 6-0, 6-3 win over Fabrice Santoro of France. Third-
seeded Yevgeny Kafelnikov of Russia powered past No. 6 American
Todd Martin 7-6 (10-8), 6-7 (3-7), 6-4, and No. 11 Thomas
Johansson of Sweden slammed unseeded Jim Courier of the United
States 6-4, 6-4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
