<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at GMT0500, August 7 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The U.S. unemployment rate remained steady in
July at 4.3 percent, matching the June number and near a three-
decade low, the Labor Department reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Department said that employers added 310,000 jobs to their
payrolls. The strength in hiring last month reflected big gains in
demand for workers at temporary help agencies, which posted their
strongest rise in 18 months. Hiring of workers also showed big
gains at restaurants, computer companies and engineering firms. (
US-Unemployment Rate)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SINGAPORE -- Bond market is booming in Singapore with corporate
debt issuance totaling 9.0 billion Singapore dollars (5.4 billion
U.S. dollars) in the first half of 1999, equal to the amount for
the whole of last year.
</P>
<P>
Singapore-dollar issues by statutory boards and foreign
entities ballooned to 4.0 billion Singapore dollars (2.4 billion U.
S. dollars) from practically nothing. (Singapore-Bond Market)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
COLOMBO -- Sri Lanka on Friday inaugurated a three-day "Women
in Business" trade fair to improve the potential of rural women to
develop their income-generation activities and standards of living.
</P>
<P>
Over 100 local and Indian women exhibited their wide-ranging
products at the fair, which is organized by Sri Lanka's Women's
Chamber of Industry and Commerce (WCIC).
</P>
<P>
The fair is expected to help rural women to expand their trade
links and also generate foreign exchange for the country. (Sri
Lanka-Women-Trade Fair)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- India's cotton yarn exports registered a positive
growth in terms of volume as well as value, for the first six
months of 1999.
</P>
<P>
According to the Commerce Ministry, cotton yarn shipments
during the period were higher at 264.17 million kilogram against
230.56 million kilogram exported in the corresponding period of
last year, an increase of 14.58 percent. (India-Cotton Exports)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- Foreign and Economic Ministers from the four
countries of the Southern Common Market (Mercosur) met here Friday
to seek a solution to the trade disputes between Argentina and
Brazil.
</P>
<P>
The Mercosur Council emergency meeting, initiated by Uruguayan
President Julio Sanguinetti, is expected to arrive at some
decisions to address the intra-zone trade distortion in the bloc
comprising Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay, following the
devaluation of Brazil's currency. (Uruguay-Mercosur-Emergency
Meeting) 
</P>
