<HEADLINE> Blast Injures Dozens at U.S. Texas Hotel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Dozens of people were injured
as a fireball exploded on Friday evening over the swimming pool of
a newly-opened hotel in Grapevine of Texas State in the United
States, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
No deaths were reported. There was no fire after the initial
blast and police said nobody had been trapped in the rubble.
</P>
<P>
The blast occurred about 6:30 p.m. (2330 GMT) in a ground floor
equipment room of the Embassy Suites hotel, which opened Tuesday
but remained under construction.
</P>
<P>
The reports quoted the hotel's manager as saying that a natural
gas line could have been responsible, but a utility spokeswoman at
the scene said she did not think gas was involved.
</P>
<P>
The reports did not give exact number of the injured.
</P>
<P>
Grapevine is a suburban community of 38,000 people north of
Dallas, near the Dallas-Fort Worth International Airport. 
</P>
