<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Weightlifter Gives Dominica First Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WINNIPEG, Canada, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Dominican Weightlifter
Wanda Rijo hoisted the country to its first gold medal after
their high jumper Juana Rosario Arrende had her title stripped of
following a positive drug test.
</P>
<P>
In the women's 75kg class, Rijo lifted 100kg in the snatch and
120kg in the clean and jerk for a combined result of 220kg,
beating American rival Cara Heads's 217.5kg into second spot.
</P>
<P>
It officially marked the first gold medal for the Dominican
Republic, from whom the Pan American Sports Organization (PASO)
decided to withdraw the women's high jump gold after Arrende
tested positive for steroid three days ago.
</P>
<P>
The women's 69kg category title went to American Lea Foreman,
who snatched 100kg and jerked 115kg for a total of 215kg.
</P>
<P>
In the men's 94kg class, Cuba's Carlos Hernandez won the gold
with a cumulative result of 382.5kg. 
</P>
</TEXT>
