<HEADLINE> Lapentti and Zabaleta Advance to Grolsch Open Semi-final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 6 (xinhua) -- South Americans Nicolas Lapentti
and Mariano Zabaleta will meet in a semi-final clash on Saturday
after winning their respective quarter-final matches Friday at the
475,000 U.S. dollars Grolsch Open ATP Tour event in Amsterdam,
Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
Number two seed Lapentti of Ecuador came back from a first set
loss to eliminate Moroccan Hicham Arazi 2-6, 7-5, 6-3, while third-
seeded Zabaleta of Argentina defeated 1991 champion Magnus
Gustafsson of Sweden 7-6 (7-3), 6-3 to advance to his second
consecutive semi-final at this event.
</P>
<P>
Sixth seed Younes El Aynaoui of Morocco and eighth-seeded
Russian Marat Safin, who won their quarter-final matches on
Thursday, will also battle it out Saturday for a place in Sunday's
final. 
</P>
</TEXT>
