<HEADLINE> Argentina Builds Holocaust Museum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Argentina will soon have a
Museum of the Holocaust in its capital city to remember the
millions of people assassinated by Nazi Germany during World War
II.
</P>
<P>
The construction of the Museum of the Shoa of Buenos Aires
started formally Thursday with the laying of the cornerstone
carved with an inscription that reads "An eternal name I will give
them that will never be erased."
</P>
<P>
Photographs, mementos, films and testimonies will be put on
display in the museum, to be the biggest of its kind in South
America.
</P>
<P>
The museum will include a teacher training center and an
institute for writing and translation of the works on the
Holocaust.
</P>
<P>
It will also have a library and the first archive of about the
almost 8,000 survivors of the genocide who arrived in Argentina.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the museum is expected to be completed in
April next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
