<HEADLINE> Angola Beats Nigeria in Africa Basketball Championship Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Angola did a better teamwork and
was strong in both attack and defense before they powered to a 79-
72 win over Nigeria in the final of the 20th African men's
basketball championships on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Under the inspiration of home crowds, Angola got off to a
strong start and powered to a first-half lead of 46-23 over
Nigeria, a young team which became prone to turnovers under the
pressure of the hosts.
</P>
<P>
Spearheaded by two players playing in National Basketball
Association of the United States, Nigeria tried to fought back
into the match by making full use of their physical stamina and
proficient ball-handling skills.
</P>
<P>
But it was a bit late for their recovery as they trailed a 7-
point margin at the final whistle.
</P>
<P>
The high-profile African event, which tipped off on July 29
here, drew a total of 12 countries and it also serve as the
African zone qualifiers for next year's Olympics. Both hosts and
Nigeria booked the berths for the Sydney Olympic Games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
