<HEADLINE> Germany Ski Jumper Thoma Retires </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The Olympic champion Diter Thoma
called it quit from international ski jumping at Hinterzarten,
Germany on Friday, citing injury during his career.
</P>
<P>
Thoma said his decision had been made after 14 years at
international level because he was tired of knee operations which
he had recieved for eight times during his career.
</P>
<P>
Thoma, 30, won a gold at the 1994 Lillehammer Winter Olympics
and also captained the German squad to the team gold medal at this
year's championships. 
</P>
</TEXT>
