<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinhua Article Exposes Lee Teng-hui's Splittist Nature </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- A signed article released by
Xinhua News Agency today said Lee Teng-hui's recent "two-states"
remarks were a thorough exposure of his long-standing attempt to
undermine the integrity of China's sovereignty and territory.
</P>
<P>
The article, entitled "Crucial Point Is to Split China",
accused Lee of sticking with splittism for a long period of time,
and even publicly opposing the "one China" principle, resulting in
serious consequences.
</P>
<P>
The article cited a spate of historical documents and facts, as
well as the practice of international law, to prove that there is
only one China and that the sovereignty of China can never be
separated or shared.
</P>
<P>
According to international law, it said, a newly-founded
government following the toppling of the former government by a
revolution should inevitably exercise all the power, including the
sovereignty, of the state. "As a matter of course, the government
of the People's Republic of China (PRC) is entitled to exercise
all power and the sovereignty of the whole of China, including
Taiwan, after the Kuomintang-led regime was overthrown in 1949."
</P>
<P>
The PRC has established diplomatic relations with more than 160
countries, which all have recognized that there is only one China,
that the government of the PRC is the sole legal government
representing the whole of China, and that Taiwan is an inseparable
part of China.
</P>
<P>
By quoting international law and the widely-accepted definition
of sovereignty, the article stressed that a state can never be
separated from its sovereignty, and the state has the right to
eliminate all separatist forces in a bid to safeguard its
territorial and sovereignty integrity.
</P>
<P>
The article also denounced the "money diplomacy" which is
advocated by Lee Teng-hui, saying that the so-called "diplomatic
relationships" between Taiwan and some 20 countries are as
unstable as a house built on sand.
</P>
<P>
The PRC has greatly strengthened its comprehensive national
power in the past few decades, and has been occupying a pivotal
position internationally. No politician with strategic foresight
and a good understanding of international situations would
sacrifice normal diplomatic relations with the PRC for relations
with Taiwan for the sake of money, the article said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
