<HEADLINE> Venezuela's Oil Price Basket Falls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Venezuelan crude price basket
registered a fall of 32 U.S. cents to 17.04 dollars per barrel
this week, the Ministry of Energy and Mines announced Friday.
</P>
<P>
The price fall, the first of its kind in the last two months,
was due to the liquidation of the contracts in the future markets,
the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of this year, oil prices have recovered 98.
5 percent. Following an output cut of 2 million barrels per day by
the oil producing countries, oil prices in the world market
started to rebound on March 12.
</P>
<P>
Venezuela's average oil price in 1998 was 10.63 dollars per
barrel.
</P>
<P>
With oil as the pillar of its economy, the country is the
largest oil producer and exporter in the Western hemisphere.
</P>
</TEXT>
