<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bomb Blasts Oil Pipeline in Northeast Colombia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- A bomb exploded Friday
at a segment of Colombia's Central Oil Pipeline in Los Llanos,
northeastern Casanare department, which the authorities said was
the work of the rebel National Liberation Army (ELN).
</P>
<P>
The blast wrecked the pipeline, paralyzed pumping and caused a
spill of some 3,000 barrels of crude, the Colombian State Oil
Company said.
</P>
<P>
The company has made a series of emergency measures to control
the serious environmental damages at the site, including rush-
repair of the pipeline.
</P>
<P>
The Central Pipeline carries crude from the Casanare oil fields
to refineries in the north of the country.
</P>
<P>
The authorities said the ELN guerrillas have so far carried out
some 1,000 attacks against oil installations across the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
