<HEADLINE> 72 Countries and Regions to Compete at Military World Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, Croatia, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Seventy-two countries and
regions will compete at the 2nd Military World Games to open at
the Croatian capital Zagreb Sunday here.
</P>
<P>
Lieutenant General Josi Lucic, Director of the Institution of
the Games, confirmed Friday morning that soldiers-athletes from
forty-six teams has arrived.
</P>
<P>
Host Croatia will feature the biggest delegation of 540 people,
followed by the United States at 350 and Italy 338.
</P>
<P>
Sports powerhouse Russia is sending a 272-person delegation
while China boasts the biggest Asian squad with 239 people,
including 145 athletes.
</P>
<P>
Altogether there would be nearly 6,500 athletes, coaches and
officials who attend the games, the organizers said.
</P>
<P>
The athletes will vie for the medals in 25 sports, including
the stamina-testing military and naval pentathlons, shooting,
swimming, orienteering, judo and wrestling.
</P>
<P>
The International Olympic Committee President Juan Antonio
Samaranch is expected to attend Sunday's opening ceremony.
</P>
</TEXT>
